#
# for authToken in fortify
#
#	how to apply an authToken in fortify
	#	This step is only required if you upload results for the first time or if the authentication token has expired 
	#	(default expiration period is 90 days, max 270 days can be specified via parameter -daysToLive 270).
	#	Execute the command:
			fortifyclient token -gettoken AnalysisUploadToken -url https://fortify1.*/ssc -user <d-user>
			fortifyclient token -gettoken AnalysisUploadToken -url https://fortify1.*/ssc -user <d-user> -daysToLive 270
	
	When asked, enter your SAP GLOBAL password and save the received token for later use.
